{{Ada/Navigation|Attributes|'Floor}}
__TOC__

== Description ==

X'Floor(Y) is an Ada [[Ada Programming/Attributes|attribute]] where X is any floating-point type and Y is any instance of that type. This attribute represents the largest integer value that is less than or equal to Y. 

== Example ==

 X : Float := 1.5;
 Y : Float := 1.0;
 Z : Float := 1.999;

 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Floor (X) = 1.0);  {{Ada/--|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Floor (Y) = 1.0);  {{Ada/--|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Floor (Z) = 2.0);  {{Ada/--|Wrong}}

== See also ==

=== Wikibook ===

* [[Ada Programming]]
* [[Ada Programming/Attributes]]
* [[Ada Programming/Attributes/'Ceiling]]
* [[Ada Programming/Attributes/'Rounding]]

=== Ada Reference Manual ===

* {{Ada/RM2|13|3|Operational and Representation Attributes}}
* {{Ada/RMA1|K|Language-Defined Attributes}}


[[Category:Ada Programming|Floor]]

{{Ada/Navigation|Attributes|'Ceiling}}
__TOC__

== Description ==

X'Ceiling(Y) is an Ada [[Ada Programming/Attributes|attribute]] where X is any floating-point type and Y is any instance of that type. This attribute represents the smallest integer value that is greater than or equal to Y. 

== Example ==

 X : Float := 1.5;
 Y : Float := 1.0;
 Z : Float := 1.999;
 ... 
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Ceiling(X) = 2.0 );  {{Ada/--|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Ceiling(Y) = 1.0 );  {{Ada/--|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Ceiling(Z) = 1.0 );  {{Ada/--|Wrong}}

