{{Ada/Navigation|Attributes|'Rounding}}
__TOC__

== Description ==

X'Rounding(Y) is an Ada [[Ada Programming/Attributes|attribute]] where X is any floating-point type and Y is any instance of that type. This attribute represents the closest integer value to Y. If Y is exactly between two integer values (e.g. 1.5), then the result is the number farthest away from zero (e.g. 1.5 => 2.0, -1.5 => -2.0). 

== Example ==

 W : Float := -1.5;
 X : Float :=  1.5;
 Y : Float :=  1.0;
 Z : Float :=  1.999;
 ...
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Rounding(W) = -2.0); {{Ada/--|OK}} 
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Rounding(X) =  2.0); {{Ada/--|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Rounding(Y) =  1.0); {{Ada/--|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Rounding(Z) =  2.0); {{Ada/--|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Rounding(W) = -1.0); {{Ada/--|Wrong}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Rounding(X) =  1.0); {{Ada/--|Wrong}}

