{{Ada/Navigation|Attributes|'Truncation}}
__TOC__

== Description ==

X'Truncation(Y) is an Ada [[Ada Programming/Attributes|attribute]] where X is any floating-point type and Y is any instance of that type. This attribute represents the truncation of Y to an integer value.

If Y is negative, then Truncation is equivalent to [[Ada Programming/Attributes/'Ceiling|X'Ceiling(Y)]]. If Y is positive, then Truncation is equivalent to [[Ada Programming/Attributes/'Floor|X'Floor(Y)]].

== Example ==

 X : Float :=  1.5;
 Y : Float :=  1.0;
 Z : Float := -1.999;

 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Truncation(X) =  1.0);  {{Template:Ada/comment|Ok}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Truncation(Y) =  1.0);  {{Template:Ada/comment|Ok}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Truncation(Z) = -1.0);  {{Template:Ada/comment|Ok}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Truncation(Z) = -2.0);  {{Template:Ada/comment|Wrong}}

