{{Ada/Navigation|Attributes|'Width}}
__TOC__

== Description ==

X'Width is an Ada [[Ada Programming/Attributes|attribute]] where X is any discrete type. This attribute represents the number of characters it takes to represent the "longest" type value using the [[Ada Programming/Attributes/'Image|X'Image]] attribute.

== Example ==

 {{Ada/kw|type}} My_Enum {{Ada/kw|is}} (Big, Bigger, Biggest);
 ...
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Enum'Image (Biggest) = "BIGGEST" );
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Enum'Width = 7); 
 {{Ada/--|Width of "BIGGEST" is seven}}
 {{Ada/--|Width of "BIG" and "BIGGER" are irrelevant.}}

